Package: varKgen
Type: Package
Title: Calibrated VAR(K) Data-Generating Processes for Interval-Specific
    Cross-Lagged Effects
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("Martin", "Hecht", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "martin.hecht@hsu-hh.de")
Description: Tools to construct bivariate VAR(K) data-generating processes
    whose model-implied population cross-lagged panel model (CLPM)
    coefficients across time intervals delta = 1, ..., delta_max match
    user-specified target profiles, jointly with the population autoregressive
    projection effects at the first target interval, one time unit ("varK
    generator"). Includes the
    companion-form construction, an exact stationary covariance solver,
    computation of implied interval-specific coefficients, multi-start
    Nelder-Mead calibration with optional BFGS polishing and parallel
    restarts, stationary panel data simulation, and OLS-based verification
    utilities.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: stats, parallel, utils
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
